2
Define & Own Growth Strategy: Develop and execute a comprehensive, data-driven growth strategy that integrates marketing, product, and operations to drive aggressive user acquisition, engagement, and retention across all Clinikally offerings.
Identify Growth Levers: Continuously identify, evaluate, and prioritize new growth opportunities, channels, and tactics, from performance marketing and SEO to partnerships, viral loops, and referral programs.
Lead & Scale Growth Teams: Build, mentor, and inspire a high-performing growth organization (which may include teams focused on user acquisition, retention, and product growth), fostering a culture of rapid experimentation, data-driven decision-making, and accountability.
Experimentation & Optimization: Implement a robust A/B testing and experimentation framework across the entire customer journey, driving continuous optimization of conversion rates and LTV.
Deep Dive into Analytics: Own growth analytics, dashboards, and reporting, providing critical insights to the leadership team and informing strategic product and business decisions.
Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner seamlessly with Product, Engineering, Marketing, and Operations teams to ensure growth initiatives are deeply integrated and supported across the organization.
Market & Consumer Insights: Maintain a deep understanding of the Indian consumer landscape, competitive dynamics, and emerging market trends to adapt and evolve growth strategies.
Budget & Resource Management: Strategically allocate and manage significant growth budgets to maximize ROI and achieve ambitious growth targets.

