7
Growth Strategy and Leadership:
• Own and drive the overall growth roadmap across acquisition, activation, retention, and monetisation.
• Develop hyper-local expansion strategies to scale in existing geographies and launch new territories rapidly.
• Build and mentor a high-performing org of growth managers, performance marketers, regional leads, and growth analysts.
• Partner closely with the CEO, CPO, Growth Head, and Ops leadership to align growth objectives with broader business goals.
Performance Marketing and Channel Ownership:
• Lead end-to-end paid marketing across Meta, Google, OEM, programmatic, affiliates, influencers, and emerging channels.
• Own multi-crore monthly marketing budgets with rigorous ROI discipline.
• Build experimentation frameworks for creatives, funnels, landing pages, onboarding flows, and retention journeys.
• Drive CAC reduction, LTV expansion, and efficiency improvements across all major channels.
Geography Expansion and Category Growth:
• Build expansion playbooks, GTM frameworks, and local growth strategies for each city/region.
• Identify high-opportunity markets and lead 01 launches with aggressive timelines.
• Scale revenue and DAUs across regions through a mix of on-ground insights, data-driven strategies, and rapid experimentation.
Product-Led Growth and New Verticals:
• Work closely with Product and Data teams to design growth loops, user journeys, and retention drivers.
• Influence product roadmap to unlock better activation, engagement, and monetisation.
• Drive launch strategies for new verticals, pricing, positioning, funnels, GTM sequencing, and scale-up mechanics.
Data, Analytics and Experimentation:
• Build a rigorous eexperimentationculture A/B testing, micro-optimisations, funnel deep dives, and user segmentation.
• Own growth dashboards and north-star metrics across geographies and verticals.
• Drive actionable insights through cohort analysis, growth accounting, and consumer behaviour mapping.
