16
Loan Pool Sourcing for Internal Collections
• Identify and acquire retail or SME loan portfolios from banks, NBFCs, fintechs, and ARCs.
• Evaluate pool suitability for internal collections, based on vintage, asset class, geography, and legal profile.
• Build strong origination relationships with institutional lenders to ensure a steady pipeline of fresh recovery opportunities.
• Coordinate with internal legal and operations teams to ensure smooth transition and integration of acquired portfolios.
• Own revenue and margin targets for both sourced and unsecured portfolios.
Business Development – Digital Collections as a Service
• Lead B2B sales efforts for the organization's digital collections platform targeting external financial institutions.
• Develop tailored commercial models (e.g., success-based, hybrid, or subscription) based on client needs.
Strategic Partnerships & Market Expansion
• Establish partnerships with fintechs, legal firms, skip tracing providers, and resolution agents.
• Expand service offerings into adjacent areas such as legal recovery, fraud detection, or analytics-driven dunning.
Team Leadership & Operational Coordination
• Manage a team of investment analysts to support pricing, pool evaluation, portfolio reporting, and performance analysis.
